courses.learning_outcomes:
(A) To introduce students to the theory and practice of constitutionalism and human rights;
(B) To explore Chinese debates about human rights, the rule of law and democracy;
(C) To explore the role and challenges facing international and local civil society activists in China;
(D) To enhance the student critical facility in applying general ideas and principles to specific problems in achieving constitutional
and human rights objectives; and
(E) To assist the student’s capacity in research, writing, presentation and critical analysis.
